(apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites (als—accessory lateral sclerite; as—apical sclerite; bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsal sclerite; ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
Connexivum small; posterior margin of tergum VII convex (
<figureCitation box="[890,1026,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Figs. 4A, C</figureCitation>
); 1ength of abdominal tergum 4.36, terga I–VIII 0.26, 0.41, 0.32, 0.32, 0.33, 0.42, 0.85, 0.74, combined lengths of terga I–VII 2.88, sterna II–VIII 0.32, 0.30, 0.32, 0.35, 0.37, 0.45, 0.49, combined lengths of sterna II–VII 2.10, posterior margin of tergum VIII with medium sized brown setae (
<figureCitation box="[469,558,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
), sternum with long black setae (
<figureCitation box="[936,1028,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Genitalia: proctiger length (insitu) 0.54; lateral process of pygophore reniform, shape more evident in alcohol due to numerous long pale to dark brown setae dorsally and ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[564,702,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Figs. 4C, D</figureCitation>
), posterior region of pygophore with numerous black adpressed spines (
<figureCitation box="[239,331,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); lateral margin of pygophore and proctiger with numerous fine setae; pygophore length, dorsal 0.21, ventral 1.68; proctiger wider than long, length 0.96, width 1.13 (after dissection), produced posterolaterally and medially, dorsally clothed with dark brown to black setae (
<figureCitation box="[872,959,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
); paramere hook-like, apical part strongly bend upward, apical inner margin slightly concave, sparse setae throughout except base and apex, subapical outer region with fringe of numerous long dark brown to black setae, inner region beyond middle with short dark brown to black setae (
<figureCitation box="[331,426,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
). Endosoma: dorsal view: basal sclerite (bs) with outer margin straight, inner margins irregular, highly sclerotised laterally; dorsal sclerite (ds) originates beneath basal sclerite, reaching near apical sclerite, basal end highly sclerotised, excavated forming lower short and upper long arms, fused behind, split before medially forming two long slender arms converging apically, apex highly sclerotised; median sclerite (ms) placed adjacent to dorsal sclerite, arising at level of subapex of lateral sclerite (ls) and apex overlaps apical sclerite; lateral sclerite placed below basal sclerite; accessory lateral sclerite (als) placed between subapices of lateral and median sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[350,442,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
); lateral view: endosoma oval shaped; bs placed over base of dorsal sclerite; ds curved, base sub-triangular; as bow-shaped; ms broad, indistinctly fused with apical sclerite; ls linear, boat-shaped; als highly sclerotised with narrow base and broad apex; ventral sclerite (vs) thin and boat-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1292,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
Fig. 
<date box="[1266,1292,836,860]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">4I</date>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1400]" box="[199,1081,871,896]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,956,871,896]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Macropterous male, apterous female and macropterous female:</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="511" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1400]" box="[199,856,908,933]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,908,933]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Distribution.</emphasis>
Peren District, 
<collectingRegion box="[528,638,908,933]" country="India" name="Nagaland" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Nagaland</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[649,709,908,933]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">India</collectingCountry>
, see 
<figureCitation box="[763,852,908,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 8" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1967,1990]" captionTargetBox="[331,1256,193,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[331,1256,193,1946]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 8A–B. Distribution in India of: A, P. nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species; B, P.tigrina Uhler (Yellow triangles denote locality details from literature; red squares denote locality details of materials examined inthe present study)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147325/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,436,943,968]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Jehamalar and Chandra" authorityName="Jehamalar &amp; Chandra &amp; Basu &amp; Selvakumar" authorityYear="2018" box="[447,974,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nagalanda" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[447,690,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Ptilomera nagalanda</emphasis>
Jehamalar and Chandra
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[989,1128,943,968]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be clearly recognized from all the known congeners from 
<collectingCountry box="[553,611,980,1005]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">India</collectingCountry>
by the absence of curly, intertwined dark brown to black swimming setae on the flexor region of the mid femur and the presence of silvery setae on the sublateral region of the meso- and metanota of the male (
<figureCitation box="[405,497,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jehamalar &amp; Chandra &amp; Basu &amp; Selvakumar" authorityYear="2018" box="[517,757,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nagalanda">
<emphasis box="[517,757,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Ptilomera nagalanda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Polhemus, 2001" authorityName="Polhemus" authorityYear="2001" box="[906,1173,1052,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fang">
<emphasis box="[906,980,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">P. fang</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus" box="[992,1173,1052,1077]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" refString="Polhemus, D. A. &amp; Polhemus, J. T. (2001) A revision of the genus Ptilomera (Heteroptera: Gerridae) on New Guinea and nearby islands. Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 109, 81 - 166. https: // doi. org / 10.1664 / 0028 - 7199 (2001) 109 [0081: AROTGP] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">Polhemus, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1244,1346,1052,1077]" name="Thailand" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, but the new species can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Polhemus" authorityYear="2001" box="[659,735,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fang">
<emphasis box="[659,735,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">P. fang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: Silvery patches are present on the first abdominal tergum in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jehamalar &amp; Chandra &amp; Basu &amp; Selvakumar" authorityYear="2018" box="[460,612,1124,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nagalanda">
<emphasis box="[460,612,1124,1148]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">P. nagalanda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[631,725,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
), whereas they are absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Polhemus" authorityYear="2001" box="[1073,1150,1124,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fang">
<emphasis box="[1073,1150,1124,1148]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">P. fang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the lateral wing of the pygophore dorsally and ventrally is clothed with white and black setae in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jehamalar &amp; Chandra &amp; Basu &amp; Selvakumar" authorityYear="2018" box="[973,1121,1160,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nagalanda">
<emphasis box="[973,1121,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">P. nagalanda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1136,1268,1159,1184]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Figs. 4C, D</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Polhemus" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fang">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">P. fang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the lateral wing of the pygophore has apical tufts of long black setae (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus" box="[1077,1256,1196,1221]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" refString="Polhemus, D. A. &amp; Polhemus, J. T. (2001) A revision of the genus Ptilomera (Heteroptera: Gerridae) on New Guinea and nearby islands. Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 109, 81 - 166. https: // doi. org / 10.1664 / 0028 - 7199 (2001) 109 [0081: AROTGP] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">Polhemus 2001</bibRefCitation>
, p. 217, Fig. 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Raruanysong" box="[151,432,1232,1257]" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" refString="Raruanysong, S., Vitheepradit, A. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2014) Key to the species of Ptilomerinae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Thailand and review of the fauna of the Tennaserim Mountain Range. Zootaxa, 3852 (1), 101 - 117. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3852.1.4" type="journal article" year="2014">
Raruanysong 
<emphasis box="[307,365,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, p. 106, Figs. 10, 11); the metasternum is distinctly shorter than the combined length of abdominal sterna II and III in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jehamalar &amp; Chandra &amp; Basu &amp; Selvakumar" authorityYear="2018" box="[485,632,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nagalanda">
<emphasis box="[485,632,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">P. nagalanda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas the metasternal length exceeds the combined lengths of sterna II and III in 
<emphasis box="[289,376,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Polhemus" authorityYear="2001" box="[289,370,1304,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fang">P. fang</taxonomicName>
;
</emphasis>
the flexor region of the mid femur basally has a fringe of short, almost straight and less dense setae reaching beyond the middle and the apex has a setal tuft (
<figureCitation box="[853,937,1340,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[226,1371,218,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[200,1376,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4A–I. Ptilomera nagalanda Jehamalar and Chandra, new species (apterous male, holotype): A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, abdominal apex, dorsal view; D, abdominal apex, ventral view; E, mid femur, ventrolateral view, showing setal fringe; F, proctiger, dorsal view; G, paramere, lateral view; H, endosoma, dorsal view, showing sclerites; I, same, lateral view, showing sclerites(als—accessorylateral sclerite;as—apical sclerite;bs—basal sclerite; ds—dorsalsclerite;ls—lateral sclerite; ms—median sclerite; vs—ventral sclerite)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1147317/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jehamalar &amp; Chandra &amp; Basu &amp; Selvakumar" authorityYear="2018" box="[980,1127,1340,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nagalanda">
<emphasis box="[980,1127,1340,1364]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">P. nagalanda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas this setal fringe is absent in 
<emphasis box="[258,342,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="511">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Polhemus" authorityYear="2001" box="[258,338,1376,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fang">P. fang</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
although it has an apical setal tuft.
</paragraph>
